2026-04-16 07:50:09 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Switch Indicator LED 1', 'Switch Indicator LED 2', 'Switch Indicator LED 3', 'Switch Indicator LED 4', 'Switch Indicator LED 5', 'Switch Indicator LED 6', 'Switch Indicator LED 7', 'Switch Indicator LED 8', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 1', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 2', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 3', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 4', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 5', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 6', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 7', 'Switch Indicator Resistor 8'] hypothesis_explanation="The symptoms described ('leds missing on all control modules' and 'lamp not turning on') together with diagnostic actions confirm that all switch indicator LEDs and their series resistors from all 8 control modules are physically missing. In the circuit design, these series LED-resistor branches provide continuity for the 12V line through each control module when the switch is ON. If all the LEDs and resistors are missing, the branch is open in each module, preventing current from flowing through the series path to the load module, so the main lamp will not light. The root cause is therefore the missing indicator LEDs and their respective resistors on all 8 control modules, breaking circuit continuity."
